{"lemma":"كَسِيرٌ","slug":"كَسِيرٌ","root":"ك.س.ر","root_slug":"ك-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-س-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36977"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"broken, crushed, shattered"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ka.siːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36977","headword_ar":"كَسِيرٌ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makosuwrN","text_ar":"مَكْسُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K,) applied to a thing: (S:) and so the fem., without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasoraY","text_ar":"كَسْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDaY","text_ar":"مَرْضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mariyDN","text_ar":"مَرِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaAraY","text_ar":"كَسَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAsiyru","text_ar":"مَكَاسِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makosuwrN","text_ar":"مَكْسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] Abu-l-Hasan says, that Sb mentions the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAsiyru","text_ar":"مَكَاسِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is of a kind proper to substs. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAqp kasiyrN","text_ar":"ناقة كَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makosuwrapN","text_ar":"مَكْسُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A broken she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K,) is like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~N xaDiybN","text_ar":"كَفٌّ خَضِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoDuwbapN","text_ar":"مَخْضُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel having one of its legs broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN kasiyrN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ كَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, having one of its legs broken:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ksyr","text_ar":"كسير"},{"kind":"text","text":"being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasiyrapN","text_ar":"كَسِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, [app. as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naTiyHapN","text_ar":"نَطِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasiyrN","text_ar":"كَسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad. is explained as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, having a broken leg, that cannot walk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, * Mgh;) but this requires consideration. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}